65// This private constructor is the central bottleneck that all the other
66// constructors use.
67LookupIterator::LookupIterator(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> receiver,
68 Handle<Name> name, size_t index,
69 Handle<Object> lookup_start_object,
70 Configuration configuration)
71 : configuration_(ComputeConfiguration(isolate, configuration, name)),
72 isolate_(isolate),
73 name_(name),
74 receiver_(receiver),
75 lookup_start_object_(lookup_start_object),
76 index_(index) {
77 if (IsElement()) {
78 // If we're not looking at a TypedArray, we will need the key represented
79 // as an internalized string.
80 if (index_ > JSObject::kMaxElementIndex &&
81 !IsJSTypedArray(*lookup_start_object, isolate_)
82#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
83 && !IsWasmArray(*lookup_start_object, isolate_)
84#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
85 ) {
86 if (name_.is_null()) {
87 name_ = isolate->factory()->SizeToString(index_);
88 }
89 name_ = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name_);
90 } else if (!name_.is_null() && !IsInternalizedString(*name_)) {
91 // Maintain the invariant that if name_ is present, it is internalized.
92 name_ = Handle<Name>();
93 }
94 Start<true>();
95 } else {
96 DCHECK(!name_.is_null());
97 name_ = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name_);
98#ifdef DEBUG
99 // Assert that the name is not an index.
100 // If we're not looking at the prototype chain and the lookup start object
101 // is not a typed array, then this means "array index", otherwise we need to
102 // ensure the full generality so that typed arrays are handled correctly.
103 if (!check_prototype_chain() && !IsJSTypedArray(*lookup_start_object)) {
104 uint32_t array_index;
105 DCHECK(!name_->AsArrayIndex(&array_index));
106 } else {
107 size_t integer_index;
108 DCHECK(!name_->AsIntegerIndex(&integer_index));
109 }
110#endif // DEBUG
111 Start<false>();
112 }
113}

115LookupIterator::LookupIterator(Isolate* isolate, Configuration configuration,
116 Handle<Object> receiver, Handle<Symbol> name)
117 : configuration_(configuration),
118 isolate_(isolate),
119 name_(name),
120 receiver_(receiver),
121 lookup_start_object_(receiver),
122 index_(kInvalidIndex) {
123 // This is the only lookup configuration allowed by this constructor because
124 // it's special case allowing lookup of the private symbols on the prototype
125 // chain. Usually private symbols are limited to OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR lookups.
126 DCHECK(*name_ == *isolate->factory()->error_stack_symbol() ||
127 *name_ == *isolate->factory()->error_message_symbol());
128 DCHECK_EQ(configuration, PROTOTYPE_CHAIN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
129 Start<false>();
130}

132PropertyKey::PropertyKey(Isolate* isolate, double index) {
133 DCHECK_EQ(index, static_cast<uint64_t>(index));
134#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_32_BIT
135 if (index <= JSObject::kMaxElementIndex) {
136 static_assert(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex <=
137 std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max());
138 index_ = static_cast<size_t>(index);
139 } else {
140 index_ = LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex;
141 name_ = isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(
142 isolate->factory()->HeapNumberToString(
143 isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber(index), index));
144 }
145#else
146 index_ = static_cast<size_t>(index);
147#endif
148}
149
150PropertyKey::PropertyKey(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Name> name, size_t index)
151 : name_(name), index_(index) {
152 DCHECK_IMPLIES(index_ == LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex, !name_.is_null());
153#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_32_BIT
154 DCHECK_IMPLIES(index_ != LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex,
155 index_ <= JSObject::kMaxElementIndex);
156#endif
157#if DEBUG
158 if (index_ != LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex && !name_.is_null()) {
159 // If both valid index and name are given then the name is a string
160 // representation of the same index.
161 size_t integer_index;
162 CHECK(name_->AsIntegerIndex(&integer_index));
163 CHECK_EQ(index_, integer_index);
164 } else if (index_ == LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex) {
165 // If only name is given it must not be a string representing an integer
166 // index.
167 size_t integer_index;
168 CHECK(!name_->AsIntegerIndex(&integer_index));
169 }
170#endif
171}
172
173PropertyKey::PropertyKey(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Name> name) {
174 if (name->AsIntegerIndex(&index_)) {
175 name_ = name;
176 } else {
177 index_ = LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex;
178 name_ = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name);
179 }
180}
181
182PropertyKey::PropertyKey(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> valid_key) {
183 DCHECK(IsName(*valid_key) || IsNumber(*valid_key));
184 if (Object::ToIntegerIndex(*valid_key, &index_)) return;
185 if (IsNumber(*valid_key)) {
186 // Negative or out of range -> treat as named property.
187 valid_key = isolate->factory()->NumberToString(valid_key);
188 }
189 DCHECK(IsName(*valid_key));
190 name_ = Handle<Name>::cast(valid_key);
191 if (!name_->AsIntegerIndex(&index_)) {
192 index_ = LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex;
193 name_ = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name_);
194 }
195}
196
197bool PropertyKey::is_element() const {
198 return index_ != LookupIterator::kInvalidIndex;
199}
200
201Handle<Name> PropertyKey::GetName(Isolate* isolate) {
202 if (name_.is_null()) {
203 DCHECK(is_element());
204 name_ = isolate->factory()->SizeToString(index_);
205 }
206 return name_;
207}

209Handle<Name> LookupIterator::name() const {
210 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!holder_.is_null(), !IsElement(*holder_));
211 return name_;
212}
213
214Handle<Name> LookupIterator::GetName() {
215 if (name_.is_null()) {
216 DCHECK(IsElement());
217 name_ = factory()->SizeToString(index_);
218 }
219 return name_;
220}
221
222PropertyKey LookupIterator::GetKey() const {
223 return PropertyKey(isolate_, name_, index_);
224}
225
226bool LookupIterator::IsElement(Tagged<JSReceiver> object) const {
227 return index_ <= JSObject::kMaxElementIndex ||
228 (index_ != kInvalidIndex &&
229 object->map()->has_any_typed_array_or_wasm_array_elements());
230}
231
232bool LookupIterator::IsPrivateName() const {
233 return !IsElement() && name()->IsPrivateName();
234}
235
236bool LookupIterator::is_dictionary_holder() const {
237 return !holder_->HasFastProperties(isolate_);
238}

256bool LookupIterator::ExtendingNonExtensible(Handle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
257 DCHECK(receiver.is_identical_to(GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>()));
258 // Shared objects have fixed layout. No properties may be added to them, not
259 // even private symbols.
260 return !receiver->map(isolate_)->is_extensible() &&
261 (IsElement() ||
262 (!name_->IsPrivate() || IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*receiver)));
263}
264
265bool LookupIterator::IsCacheableTransition() {
266 DCHECK_EQ(TRANSITION, state_);
267 return IsPropertyCell(*transition_, isolate_) ||
268 (transition_map()->is_dictionary_map() &&
269 !GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>()->HasFastProperties(isolate_)) ||
270 IsMap(transition_map()->GetBackPointer(isolate_), isolate_);
271}

273// static
274void LookupIterator::UpdateProtector(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> receiver,
275 Handle<Name> name) {
276 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kUpdateProtector);
277 DCHECK(IsInternalizedString(*name) || IsSymbol(*name));
278
279 // This check must be kept in sync with
280 // CodeStubAssembler::CheckForAssociatedProtector!
281 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
282 bool maybe_protector = roots.IsNameForProtector(*name);
283
284#if DEBUG
285 bool debug_maybe_protector =
286 *name == roots.constructor_string() || *name == roots.next_string() ||
287 *name == roots.resolve_string() || *name == roots.then_string() ||
288 *name == roots.is_concat_spreadable_symbol() ||
289 *name == roots.iterator_symbol() || *name == roots.species_symbol() ||
290 *name == roots.match_all_symbol() || *name == roots.replace_symbol() ||
291 *name == roots.split_symbol() || *name == roots.to_primitive_symbol() ||
292 *name == roots.valueOf_string();
293 DCHECK_EQ(maybe_protector, debug_maybe_protector);
294#endif // DEBUG
295
296 if (maybe_protector) {
297 InternalUpdateProtector(isolate, receiver, name);
298 }
299}
300
301void LookupIterator::UpdateProtector() {
302 if (IsElement()) return;
303 UpdateProtector(isolate_, receiver_, name_);
304}

306InternalIndex LookupIterator::descriptor_number() const {
307 DCHECK(!holder_.is_null());
308 DCHECK(!IsElement(*holder_));
309 DCHECK(has_property_);
310 DCHECK(holder_->HasFastProperties(isolate_));
311 return number_;
312}

314InternalIndex LookupIterator::dictionary_entry() const {
315 DCHECK(!holder_.is_null());
316 DCHECK(!IsElement(*holder_));
317 DCHECK(has_property_);
318 DCHECK(!holder_->HasFastProperties(isolate_));
319 return number_;
320}

322// static
323LookupIterator::Configuration LookupIterator::ComputeConfiguration(
324 Isolate* isolate, Configuration configuration, Handle<Name> name) {
325 return (!name.is_null() && name->IsPrivate()) ? OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR
326 : configuration;
327}

329// static
330MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> LookupIterator::GetRoot(
331 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> lookup_start_object, size_t index,
332 Configuration configuration) {
333 if (IsJSReceiver(*lookup_start_object, isolate)) {
334 return Handle<JSReceiver>::cast(lookup_start_object);
335 }
336 return GetRootForNonJSReceiver(isolate, lookup_start_object, index,
337 configuration);
338}

340template <class T>
341Handle<T> LookupIterator::GetStoreTarget() const {
342 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*receiver_, isolate_));
343 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver_, isolate_)) {
344 Tagged<HeapObject> prototype =
345 JSGlobalProxy::cast(*receiver_)->map(isolate_)->prototype(isolate_);
346 if (IsJSGlobalObject(prototype, isolate_)) {
347 return handle(JSGlobalObject::cast(prototype), isolate_);
348 }
349 }
350 return Handle<T>::cast(receiver_);
351}
352
353template <bool is_element>
354Tagged<InterceptorInfo> LookupIterator::GetInterceptor(
355 Tagged<JSObject> holder) const {
356 if (is_element && index_ <= JSObject::kMaxElementIndex) {
357 return holder->GetIndexedInterceptor(isolate_);
358 } else {
359 return holder->GetNamedInterceptor(isolate_);
360 }
361}
362
363inline Handle<InterceptorInfo> LookupIterator::GetInterceptor() const {
364 DCHECK_EQ(INTERCEPTOR, state_);
365 Tagged<JSObject> holder = JSObject::cast(*holder_);
366 Tagged<InterceptorInfo> result = IsElement(holder)
367 ? GetInterceptor<true>(holder)
368 : GetInterceptor<false>(holder);
369 return handle(result, isolate_);
370}
